Germany Will Close 25% of Shipping Offices, Scheurle Tells VDI

-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 
2011-06-02T10:07:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/germany-will-close-25-of-shipping-offices-scheurle-tells-vdi.html
Klaus-Dieter Scheurle,  Germany ’s
deputy transport minister, said 25 percent of the country’s
shipping offices are to be closed, VDI Nachrichten reported,
citing an interview.  Scheurle told VDI that the 40 offices will be reduced to
about 30 through mergers. About 2,800 of the 13,315 jobs at the
offices will be cut by 2020, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Frankfurt at 
 jcruz6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at   arummer@bloomberg.net  